```

No matter what in this scenario the addr used in `send({from:addr}` is paying for the airdrop. So what happens if there isn't a referral param with an address? Lets see what `airinput` is.

```html
<input id="airinput" class="form-control" required="required" placeholder="Referrer Id" type="text" hidden="">
```

The `airinput` value is hidden and set to `""`  by default so if someone went to claim the fake airdrop the tokens and eth would be sent to the owner of this scam contract.

Both of these contracts were verified, this goes to show you should verify what a contract is doing yourself before signing any transaction with your wallet.

